<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Mixed; Dow Down 26.92  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq composite index reached a new closing  
high today amid a rally in technology stocks that was spurred by a 
tame inflation report and a strong earnings outlook from computer 
chip maker Intel. Blue chip stocks failed to keep pace, falling on 
profit-taking and nervousness about economic and political 
uncertainty overseas. The Nasdaq composite rose 39.14 to 2,817.37, 
topping its record close reached last Friday. The Dow Jones 
industrial average was down 26.92 at 11,148.10, adding to its 
26-point drop on Tuesday. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 
4.60 at 1,398.16. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close  
