<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Entertainment Highlights in History  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Entertainment highlights during the week of July 18-24:  
</P>
<P>
	60 years ago: Gary Cooper, Ray Milland and Robert Preston  
starred in ``Beau Geste,'' directed by William Wellman. 
</P>
<P>
	55 years ago: Producer David O. Selznick's ``Since You Went  
Away'' starred Jennifer Jones, Claudette Colbert, Joseph Cotten and 
Shirley Temple. 
</P>
<P>
	50 years ago: The Hollywood Reporter said teen-agers were  
calling drive-in movie theaters the ``passion pits.'' 
</P>
<P>
	45 years ago: Elvis Presley's first single was released by Sun  
Records. ``That's All Right (Mama)'' was backed by ``Blue Moon of 
Kentucky.'' Both songs were hits in Memphis, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
	35 years ago: The Rolling Stones had to run for safety after the  
audience at a concert in Blackpool, England, mobbed the stage. 
</P>
<P>
	25 years ago: Charles Bronson starred in ``Death Wish.''  
</P>
<P>
	10 years ago: Ringo Starr reached out to a new generation of  
rockers by letting kids in free to his first-ever solo concert. But 
the crowd in Dallas was dominated by those who were teen-agers in 
the former Beatle's heyday. 
</P>
<P>
	And folk singer Joan Baez sang a new song protesting recent  
violence in China. The performance was at a charity concert at 
Birmingham, England, attended by Prince Charles and Princess Diana. 
</P>
<P>
	Five years ago: A sold-out crowd cheered as Billy Joel and Elton  
John sang duets and performed each other's songs at a concert in 
East Rutherford, N.J. More than 54,000 fans turned out at Giants 
Stadium for the duo's greatest hits concert. 
</P>
<P>
	And Charles Kuralt, the retired host of ``Sunday Morning,'' was  
honored by the Television Critics Association with a career 
achievement award. His 37 years with CBS included his ``On the 
Road'' reports, stories he found in out-of-the-way places while 
traveling in a van. 
</P>
<P>
	One year ago: ``Baywatch'' star David Hasselhoff celebrated his  
46th birthday by plummeting from an airplane. His jump included a 
60-second free fall before his chute opened and he landed at the 
airport in Van Nuys, Calif. It was his first parachute jump. 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken 10 years ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not monosyllabic. I'm not that quiet. I'm not a loner by  
nature.'' -- Actor Sylvester Stallone, referring to his ``Rambo'' 
roles. 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken one year ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``All the big stars have bombs. My goal, obviously, is to get to  
the point where I can pick up some supporting roles in movies, and 
maybe star in some movies, but not the stuff I've been doing.'' -- 
Actor Tom Arnold, referring to his two flop films, ``The Stupids'' 
and ``Big Bully.'' 

</P>
<P>
	``I've never been a `get up, drink coffee, read the paper' kind  
of girl. I try to stay in bed for at least 10 minutes to ponder my 
place in the universe. Then I wash my face, check my karma and get 
my balance for the day. Then I can go out into the universe with a 
positive attitude.'' -- Actress Drew Barrymore. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
