<HEADLINE> Brazil 2, Mexico 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASUNCION, Paraguay, (AP) -- Amoroso and Rivaldo scored goals  
Wednesday night and Brazil beat Mexico 2-0 in a semifinal game in 
the Copa America soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Uruguay, which beat Chile 5-3 on penalty kicks after the teams  
finished 1-1 Tuesday night, plays Brazil in the championship game 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The expected shootout between the tournament's two most potent  
attacks turned out to be one-sided, as the Brazilians shut down 
Mexico's Luis Hernandez and Co. 
</P>
<P>
	Mexico's strategy of taking the fight to the Brazilians  
foundered on a tough defense and gave Ronaldo and teammates all the 
space they needed to unveil their repertoire of dribbles, no-looks 
and touch passes. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 25th minute, Ze Roberto zoomed to the baseline and  
crossed to Rivaldo, who put a header on the post. The ball caromed 
out to Amoroso in the middle of the goal, and he tapped it in for a 
1-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 44th minute, Rivaldo found Ronaldo at the top of the  
penalty area, where he was tripped. Rivaldo picked up the loose 
ball and fired it into the left corner to make it 2-0. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
