<HEADLINE> Fla. Murder Suspect Pleads Innocent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARASOTA, Fla. (AP) -- A man extradited from Mexico on a murder  
charge pleaded innocent Wednesday to killing a woman while her 
quadruplet toddlers were with her at home, leaving them to crawl in 
her blood. 
</P>
<P>
	Jose Luis Del Toro, a U.S. citizen, submitted a written plea and  
was ordered held without bond. 
</P>
<P>
	Del Toro, 23, is accused of shooting Sheila Bellush and slitting  
her throat while she was home with the 2-year-olds in a 
murder-for-hire plot in November 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Bellush, and the children covered in her blood, were found  
by her teen-age daughter. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors persuaded Mexican officials to send Del Toro back to  
the United States by agreeing not to seek the death penalty, which 
Mexico does not have. Two men already are in prison for their roles 
in Mrs. Bellush's slaying. 
  	   	
</P>
