<HEADLINE> Singer Durst Arrested for Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- Fred Durst, lead singer for the rap-metal  
band Limp Bizkit, was arrested for allegedly kicking a security 
guard in the head on stage during a concert. 
</P>
<P>
	Durst, 28, was taken into cusgtody but not charged Monday night  
after Limp Bizkit finished its performance. He was released on 
$50,000 bail. The case was referred to the city attorney's office 
for possible misdemeanor charges. 
</P>
<P>
	The security guard was treated for minor injuries.  
</P>
<P>
	``Durst was somewhat apologetic,'' said police spokesman Michael  
Jordan. ``It seems to be a case of mistaken identity. Durst thought 
his guy was getting beat up by two fans, and that's when he kicked 
the guy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Durst was unavailable for comment. His band is touring and had a  
concert Tuesday night in Chicago. 
  	   	
