<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Egghead, Onsale Plan Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MENLO PARK, Calif. (AP) -- Onsale Inc. and Egghead.com Inc. have  
agreed to merge in a $390.3 million stock deal that unites two 
online sellers of computer hardware and software, the companies 
announced today. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement calls for Egghead.com stockholders to exchange  
each of their shares for 0.565 Onsale shares, Dow Jones News 
Service reported. 
</P>
<P>
	Following the exchange, current Egghead.com shareholders will  
own about 47 percent of the combined company. 
</P>
<P>
	The new company, to be headquartered in Menlo Park, Calif., will  
operate under the Egghead.com name and Internet address with 
auctions and sales of surplus goods under the Onsale banner. 
</P>
<P>
	Menlo Park-based Onsale lost $14.7 million on sales of $207.8  
million in 1998. Vancouver, Wash.-based Egghead.com lost $34.4 
million on sales of $148.7 million in the year ended April 3. 
</P>
<P>
	In morning trading, shares of Onsale changed hands at $21.875,  
down 62.5 cents, on the Nasdaq Stock Market. Meanwhile, Egghead.com 
shares traded at $12.375, up 37.5 cents, also on the Nasdaq. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
