<HEADLINE> George Lucas High School Damaged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MODESTO, Calif. (AP) -- George Lucas' high school, the  
inspiration for the world of sock hops and ducktail haircuts in 
``American Graffiti,'' was damaged in an electrical fire. 
</P>
<P>
	The four-alarm blaze before dawn Tuesday gutted three classrooms  
and damaged other rooms in a wing at Downey High School. No one was 
in the building at the time. Damage was put at $1.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators said the blaze started in newly installed,  
low-voltage Internet wiring in a wall. 
</P>
<P>
	Lucas, a 1962 graduate of Downey High, based 1973's ``American  
Graffiti,'' his first big hit, on his hometown. 
</P>
<P>
	The high school has been dubbed ``American Graffiti High.''  
  	   	
</P>
