<HEADLINE> Plane Makes Emergency Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- An American Airlines jet made an emergency landing  
at a naval station in the Florida Keys after the pilot said he 
smelled smoke aboard the Miami-to-Cancun flight with 162 people 
aboard. 
</P>
<P>
	No one was injured, but passengers said flight attendants paced  
throughout the plane with fire extinguishers. Children wept and 
older passengers prayed. 
</P>
<P>
	Flight 2191 landed at about 2:45 p.m. EDT Tuesday at the Key  
West Naval Air Station at Boca Chica Key, airline spokeswoman 
Martha Pantin said. 
</P>
<P>
	The pilot and crew only smelled smoke and did not see it, Pantin  
said. Several passengers, who said the trouble began just as the 
crew started to serve food, saw a slight fog in the cabin. 
</P>
<P>
	``That was the worst anguish -- when they say we are going to  
land and you look out the window and you see the ocean,'' said Mayi 
Antillon, 38, of San Jose, Costa Rica. 
</P>
<P>
	Pantin said another Boeing 757 was sent to the island to take  
the passengers to Cancun. The evacuated jet was to be taken to 
Miami International Airport to be inspected by airline maintenance 
workers. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
