<HEADLINE> Jim Leyland Has Elbow Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Colorado Rockies manager Jim Leyland is recovering  
from surgery after doctors here removed a cyst the size of a grape 
from his right elbow on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``They weren't expecting that,'' Leyland said from his home in  
Pittsburgh, where he is recuperating. ``It was right in the groove 
of the nerve. It took a little longer than they expected, but there 
wasn't any problem.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Leyland said he will wear a sling for several weeks but will be  
in uniform at Cinergy Field in Cincinnati on Thursday as Colorado 
resumes play after the All-Star break. 
</P>
<P>
	Leyland said he had been bothered by a loss of feeling in his  
hand since spring training. 
</P>
<P>
	He said he had planned to wait until after the season for  
surgery, but doctors told him he risked losing muscle control in 
his right hand if he waited. 
  	   	
</P>
