<HEADLINE> Hydro Association President Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Bob Gobrecht has resigned as president and chief  
executive officer of the Unlimited Hydroplane Racing Association, 
less than 10 months after taking the job. 
</P>
<P>
	The departure of Gobrecht, 48, marks the association's fourth  
change of command in two years. 
</P>
<P>
	Ken Muscatel of Seattle, the sport's acting commissioner, will  
be interim president. 
</P>
<P>
	``The sport is in much better shape than it was last fall, and  
it's in very capable hands with Dr. Muscatel,'' Gobrecht said. 
</P>
<P>
	The hydros will be a client of Gobrecht's California-based  
sports marketing business. He said he will now have time to find a 
major sponsor for the races. 
</P>
<P>
	There are seven races remaining on the 12-race schedule.  
</P>
<P>
	Commissioner Bill Doner resigned last summer. Ned Allen and  
Muscatel each ran the organization briefly before Gobrecht was 
hired. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
