<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Braves Promote Balderson As Exec </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The Atlanta Braves promoted Dick Balderson to  
director of player development on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Balderson, 53, has spent two seasons as a major league scout for  
the Braves following a six-year stint with the Colorado Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Rockies, Balderson was director of player development  
from 1992-94 and vice president of player personnel from 1995-97. 
</P>
<P>
	He also has served as director of scouting and player  
development for the Kansas City Royals, vice president of baseball 
operations for the Seattle Mariners and vice president of scouting 
and player development for the Chicago Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
	Balderson replaced Paul Snyder, who relinquished his dual role  
as director of player development and scouting director in June. 
Roy Clark was named director of scouting last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
