<DOCNO> APW19990714.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 16:00:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Intel Restructures Business Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- To increase its focus on Internet  
opportunities, Intel announced Wednesday it would restructure 
several of its business groups. 
</P>
<P>
	The new Communications Products Group will emerge from the  
combination of related hardware, software and support groups. 
</P>
<P>
	``Intel is organizing around Internet opportunities in four key  
areas,'' said Intel chief executive officer Craig R. Barrett. ``The 
addition of the (CPG) segments our network infrastructure 
activities along systems and components.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The CPG will bring together the Communications and Internet  
Server Division, the Dialogic subsidiary, the Network Systems 
Division and the Systems Management Division. The new group will be 
headed by John H.F. Miner, an Intel vice president. 
</P>
<P>
	Recently, Intel formed the Platform Components Group by  
combining the Platform Components Division, Graphics Components 
Division, Platform Driver Division and the Intel Architechture 
Business Group. The PCG is headed by Intel vice president and 
general manager Louis J. Burns. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
