<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Maple Leaf Coach Quinn Also To Be GM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Coach Pat Quinn of the Toronto Maple Leafs has  
added the general manager's job to his duties. 
</P>
<P>
	Quinn, who at one time held the dual role in Vancouver, replaces  
Ken Dryden, the team's president. 
</P>
<P>
	``Last year we were fifth overall in the league and reached the  
final four,'' Dryden said. 
</P>
<P>
	``But we still have a long way to go. I think Pat is the one who  
can see us through the next difficult steps and get us there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Quinn said his priority would still be coaching.  
</P>
<P>
	``To me, I'm still the coach and that's my prime responsibility.  
It's just that my focus on that job changes a little bit,'' he 
said. ``I hope to be able to still have my coach's hat and when the 
opportunity for a bigger picture of the organization comes into 
place I hope to do that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The job became open when Dryden didn't rehire associate GM Mike  
Smith last month. Dryden had the GM title but Smith had been the de 
facto general manager, making all personnel moves. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
