<HEADLINE> White Sox Recall Simmons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago White Sox recalled outfielder Brian  
Simmons from Class AAA Charlotte on Wednesday and optioned first 
baseman-outfielder Jeff Liefer to Charlotte. 
</P>
<P>
	Simmons, 25, was hitting .270 with 10 homers, 53 runs and 44  
RBIs in 78 games for the Knights. Over his last 20 games, he batted 
.333 with four homers and 19 RBIs. He started the 1999 season on 
the disabled list with a hand injury suffered in spring training. 
</P>
<P>
	On Sept. 26, 1998 at Kansas City, Simmons became the third  
player in club history to homer from both sides. 
</P>
<P>
	In 39 games with Chicago, Liefer, 24, batted .237 with no home  
runs and 12 RBIs. He has not started since July 1. 
  	   	
