<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	Actress Jennifer Lopez, born on July 24, 1970, has a new  
English-language album, ``On the Six,'' which features a duet with 
Puerto Rican salsa singer Marc Anthony. ``If You Had My Love,'' one 
of the songs from the album, has topped Billboard magazine's pop 
singles chart in recent weeks. 

</P>
<P>
	John Leguizamo, born on July 22, 1964, is one of the stars of  
Spike Lee's new film, ``Summer of Sam.'' Last year, Leguizamo's 
one-man show ``Freak'' was nominated for two Tony Awards. 

</P>
<P>
	Carlos Santana, born on July 20, 1947, received a special  
achievement award at the 1999 American Latino Media Arts Awards. 
The annual awards are presented to actors, actresses, television 
hosts and musical performers who portray positive Hispanic images. 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays for July 18-24:  
</P>
<P>
	July 18: Actor James Brolin is 59. Singer Martha Reeves of  
Martha and the Vandellas is 58. Musician Nigel Twist of The Alarm 
is 41. Actress Elizabeth McGovern is 38. Musician John Hermann of 
