<HEADLINE> 160 Children Get Sick at W.Va. Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MORGANTOWN, W.Va. (AP) -- Scores of children at a summer camp  
became violently ill with vomiting and diarrhea, and investigators 
are trying to determine what happened. 
</P>
<P>
	About 100 children got severely sick at the Emma Kaufmann Camp  
in Stewartstown on July 5, and on Wednesday another 60 had fallen 
ill, Monongalia County Health Department Administrator Ed Phillips 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Most are recovering and officials asked parents to leave their  
children at the camp to help contain the outbreak and identify its 
source. Investigators from the Centers for Disease Control are 
helping officials determine the cause. 
</P>
<P>
	The outbreak has been confined to the camp with the exception of  
a few children who went home and passed the illness to their 
families, leading health officials to believe the outbreak is a 
virus nor passed on through food, Phillips said. 
  	   	
</P>
