<HEADLINE> TV Carts Recalled for Tip-Over Risk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 100,000 television carts, some up to 7  
years old, are being recalled because they can tip over, the 
Consumer Product Safety Commission said today. 
</P>
<P>
	The manufacturer, Bush Industries, has received two reports of  
tipping carts, one resulting in a minor injury, the commission 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The ready-to-assemble carts are laminated in black or brown and  
were sold in discount, home and furniture stores nationwide from 
June 1992 to August 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Consumers should remove their televisions and VCRs from the  
carts immediately, the commission warned. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush Industries asks consumers to call 800-950-4782 to receive a  
free repair kit to help prevent cart tip-over. 

  	   	
</P>
