<HEADLINE> Senate Confirms New Treasury Deputy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Senate voted unanimously Tuesday to  
confirm Stuart Eizenstat as the Treasury Department's deputy 
secretary. 
</P>
<P>
	Eizenstat was a top economic affairs official at the State  
Department when President Clinton nominated him to succeed Lawrence 
Summers at Treasury. 
</P>
<P>
	Summers, a former Harvard economist, became the nation's 71st  
treasury secretary on July 2, when he was sworn in to replace 
Robert Rubin, who resigned. 
</P>
<P>
	The Senate also by voice vote Tuesday night confirmed Clinton's  
nomination of T. John Ward to be a U.S. District Judge for the 
Eastern District of Texas. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
