<HEADLINE> Catcher Casanova Assigned to Toledo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- The Detroit Tigers assigned catcher Raul Casanova  
to Triple A Toledo after he was reinstated from the 60-day disabled 
list and cleared waivers. 
</P>
<P>
	Casanova has been on the disabled list since March 31 and had  
surgery April 7 to repair a broken rib caused by a benign tumor. 
</P>
<P>
	On June 24, Casanova began an injury rehabilitation assignment  
with the Golf Coast League Tigers. His rehab continued in Lakeland 
and he was transferred to Toledo on July 4. 
</P>
<P>
	Casanova has played in 142 games with Detroit the past three  
seasons, hitting .223 with 10 home runs and 36 RBIs. 
  	   	
